    "recap_headline": "Xavier University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "CINCINNATI\n- Xavier baseball fell in the series finale with Evansville, 5-1, on Sunday afternoon at Hayden Field. The Purple Aces took the series, 2-1, with the win.\nThe Musketeers moved to 6-15 on the year, while the Purple Aces moved to 5-13.\nEvansville got on the board in the first inning with a pair of runs, and added two more in the third to take a 4-0 lead. In the bottom of the third,\nMitchell Morton\nled off the frame with a single, and after\nJD Crisp\nreached on a fielders choice, a walk from\nJorge Valdes\nand a single from\nClay Burdette\nloaded the bases with one out.\nJosh Stonehouse\nbrought Crisp in from third with a sac fly to get the Musketeers on the board.\nAshton Chronister\nmade the start on the mound for the Musketeers, going a career-long 7.0 innings, not allowing a run after the third, and finishing with a career-best six strikeouts before exiting for the eighth. The 4-1 advantage for Evansville held into the eighth when the Purple Aces picked up another run to set the final score at 5-1.\nThe Musketeers remain at home to host Ohio State on Wednesday, March 18, set for a 3:00 p.m. start at Hayden Field. The game with the Buckeyes will be streamed live on XAVIER+.\nAT THE PLATE\nJosh Stonehouse\nrecorded an RBI with a sac fly.\nJD Crisp\nscored a run after getting aboard on a fielder's choice.\nDonavan Canterberry\nwent 2-3 with a walk.\nClay Burdette\nfinished 2-4 at the plate.\nLuke Hammond\n(1-4) got on with a double.\nMitchell Morton\ngot on with a hit, and\nJorge Valdes\ngot aboard with a walk.\non the mound\nAshton Chronister\nmade his fourth start of the season, going 7.0 innings, a career-long outing for the junior, allowing four runs on eight hits and one walk, striking out a career-best six along the way.\nMichael Murphy\npitched the eighth, allowing one run on one hit and two walks in 1.0 inning of work.\nJoey Arend\npitched the ninth, not allowing a run or a hit, issuing one walk and striking out a pair.\nHIGHLIGHTS"
